From 292314d674382cacb54f41324523ddbc802126c7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: 10BE Software UG <support@ns.10be.de>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 15:30:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Allow 10BE CarbCam to prefill the AddCarbs sheet via URL
 scheme

Adds a custom URL scheme handler that lets 10BE CarbCam open the
standard AddCarbs sheet with the carbs (and optional notes) field
prefilled.

Design notes:

  * URL scheme: carbcam-iaps://carbs?value=<int>&notes=<str>&source=<str>
  * Carbs are bounds-checked to 1..80 g; out-of-range values are
    silently rejected. Larger meals can be adjusted manually in the
    sheet afterwards.
  * iAPS reuses its existing handleURL switch in FreeAPSApp and the
    same NotificationCenter-based dispatch pattern that the Garmin
    Connect integration already uses.
  * The AddCarbs sheet is opened via the existing HomeStateModel
    addCarbs() entry point; AddCarbsStateModel consumes the prefill
    in its subscribe() lifecycle so the value is gone after one use.
  * No insulin is ever delivered without the standard iAPS bolus
    confirmation flow.

Cold-start safe: if the URL arrives before HomeStateModel has
subscribed to the notification, the prefill is held in a static
holder and HomeStateModel.subscribe() opens AddCarbs from there.

Target branch: zehnBE/iAPS main
